  "market_context": "Crude Oil on the 1H chart formed a candle 2 closure near 89.50, establishing an hourly change in state of delivery. Previous day low (around 84.00) was marked as the draw on liquidity. Standard deviation projections (-1, -2, -2.5) were drawn but the manipulation leg was too large for them to fit cleanly within the range.",
  "key_observation": "Because the manipulation was very large, standard deviation targets did not make sense; the analyst instead targeted the previous day low. After aggressive displacement lower, entering on the initial reversal would mean an oversized stop, so a retest entry off a high sweep / order block was preferred.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the hourly change in state of delivery confirming the reversal at the C2 high.",
    "Noted that the manipulation leg was so large that standard deviation projections did not fit, so targeted the previous day low (~84.00) marked by the indicator instead.",
    "Watched price trade lower but did not trust the initial high to hold, so waited for a more convincing run.",
    "Observed a move higher followed by aggressive displacement lower that fell just shy of the previous day low.",
    "Identified a series of up-close candles retracing into an important level — a sweep of the prior high to the left — forming a valid opposing candle / order block.",
    "Rejected entering with stop on the swing high because the aggressive displacement made the R:R to the first target poor; opted instead for a retest entry at the order block.",
    "Got tagged in on the retest, saw another closure below confirming continuation, with invalidation if the high were reclaimed.",
    "Price delivered continuation lower toward the previous day low target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation lower delivered after the retest entry, reaching toward the previous day low target.",
  "lessons": "When manipulation is unusually large, swap standard deviation targets for the previous day high/low. After aggressive displacement, avoid chasing the initial reversal — wait for a retest at a high sweep + order block to size the stop properly and preserve favorable R:R.",
